<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="425" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d425">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 342.112Sm6/—.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Vice Consul <persName type="to">Curtis</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-28">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 28, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Answering yours. Take charge of body of Smith and notify relatives. Give
                            every possible care to Dorsch, the wounded man. Get statement from
                            Dorsch and any other persons knowing the facts; also statement from
                            private who did the shooting and report fully.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>